"A"

782
00:51:27,501 --> 00:51:29,252
DEXTER:
All right, here we go.

783
00:51:29,503 --> 00:51:31,546
- Quiet!
MAN: Quiet.

784
00:51:31,714 --> 00:51:33,131
Roll 'em!

785
00:51:35,968 --> 00:51:38,845
Oh, Pierre. You shouldn't have come.

786
00:51:39,096 --> 00:51:42,974
She's gotta talk into the mike.
I can't pick it up.

787
00:51:44,101 --> 00:51:45,351
Cut!

788
00:51:45,561 --> 00:51:46,728
DON:
What's the matter?

789
00:51:46,937 --> 00:51:47,979
DEXTER:
It's Lina.

790
00:51:48,230 --> 00:51:51,357
Look, Lina, don't you remember?
I told you.

791
00:51:51,609 --> 00:51:54,360
There's a microphone right there...

792
00:51:54,612 --> 00:51:56,946
- ...in the bush.
- Yeah.

793
00:51:57,114 --> 00:51:59,032
You have to talk into it.

794
00:51:59,283 --> 00:52:01,659
I was talking.
Wasn't I, Miss Dinsmore?

795
00:52:01,869 --> 00:52:05,913
Yes, my dear. But please remember,
round tones.

796
00:52:06,123 --> 00:52:09,417
"Pierre, you shouldn't have come."

797
00:52:09,668 --> 00:52:11,961
Pierre, you shouldn't have come.

798
00:52:12,212 --> 00:52:13,379
That's much better...

799
00:52:13,589 --> 00:52:15,298
Hold it a second.

800
00:52:15,507 --> 00:52:17,216
Now, Lina, look.

801
00:52:17,426 --> 00:52:18,635
Here's the mike.

802
00:52:18,886 --> 00:52:21,137
Right here in the bush.

803
00:52:21,305 --> 00:52:22,347
Yeah.

804
00:52:22,514 --> 00:52:24,015
Now, you talk towards it.

805
00:52:24,266 --> 00:52:27,268
The sound goes through the cable
to the box.

806
00:52:27,519 --> 00:52:31,147
A man records it
on a big record in wax...

807
00:52:31,398 --> 00:52:35,068
...but you have to talk
into the mike first.

808
00:52:35,277 --> 00:52:36,569
In the bush!

809
00:52:36,820 --> 00:52:38,112
Now try it again.

810
00:52:38,405 --> 00:52:39,447
Gee, this is dumb.

811
00:52:39,657 --> 00:52:41,741
She'll get it, Dexter.
Don't worry.

812
00:52:41,992 --> 00:52:45,119
We're all nervous the first day.
Everything will be okay.

813
00:52:45,412 --> 00:52:47,914
By the way. You know the scene
coming up where I say:

814
00:52:48,123 --> 00:52:50,041
"Imperious princess of the night"?

815
00:52:50,250 --> 00:52:53,836
I don't like those lines.
Is it all right if I say what I always do?

816
00:52:54,046 --> 00:52:56,547
"I love you. I love you. I love you."

817
00:52:56,799 --> 00:52:59,050
Sure. Any way it's comfortable.

818
00:52:59,259 --> 00:53:00,802
But into the bush!

819
00:53:00,969 --> 00:53:02,011
Okay.

820
00:53:02,179 --> 00:53:03,221
Again!

821
00:53:03,430 --> 00:53:04,764
Quiet!

822
00:53:05,140 --> 00:53:06,516
Roll 'em!

823
00:53:11,105 --> 00:53:13,314
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

824
00:53:19,071 --> 00:53:20,113
Cut!

825
00:53:20,572 --> 00:53:22,657
We're missing every other word.

826
00:53:22,950 --> 00:53:25,159
You've got to talk into the mike!

827
00:53:25,452 --> 00:53:27,829
Well, I can't make love to a bush!

828
00:53:28,080 --> 00:53:30,123
All right, all right.

829
00:53:30,749 --> 00:53:34,127
We'll have to think of something else.

830
00:53:39,717 --> 00:53:41,008
What are you doing?

831
00:53:41,260 --> 00:53:43,720
- You're being wired for sound.
- What?

832
00:53:43,971 --> 00:53:47,849
Watch out for those dentalized D's
and T's and those flat A's.

833
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:50,226
Everybody's picking on me.

834
00:53:50,394 --> 00:53:51,477
Okay, Lina.

835
00:53:51,645 --> 00:53:53,896
Now look at this flower, see?

836
00:53:54,148 --> 00:53:55,982
The mike is in there.

837
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:57,900
That's it.

838
00:53:58,110 --> 00:54:00,820
The sound will run from it...

839
00:54:01,280 --> 00:54:03,865
...through this wire, onto the record.

840
00:54:04,074 --> 00:54:06,200
It'll catch whatever you say.

841
00:54:06,410 --> 00:54:09,579
Now let's hear how it sounds, Lina.

842
00:54:10,038 --> 00:54:12,248
Okay, quiet!

843
00:54:12,499 --> 00:54:13,875
Roll 'em!

844
00:54:16,712 --> 00:54:18,796
Oh, Pierre, you shouldn't have come.

845
00:54:18,964 --> 00:54:20,131
[HEART BEATING]

846
00:54:20,299 --> 00:54:22,508
You're flirting with danger.

847
00:54:23,761 --> 00:54:24,761
What's that noise?

848
00:54:25,012 --> 00:54:26,763
It's picking up her heartbeat.

849
00:54:27,014 --> 00:54:28,514
Swell.

850
00:54:29,433 --> 00:54:30,516
Cut!

851
00:54:34,813 --> 00:54:37,064
That's right. That should do it.

852
00:54:37,316 --> 00:54:38,733
Now, don't forget.

853
00:54:38,942 --> 00:54:40,943
The mike is on your shoulder.

854
00:54:41,195 --> 00:54:44,822
And whatever you say goes
through the wire onto the record.

855
00:54:45,073 --> 00:54:48,117
Now, please, Lina, talk into the mike.

856
00:54:48,368 --> 00:54:51,662
Don't make any quick movements
or you might disconnect it.

857
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:53,372
Okay, let's go.

858
00:54:53,624 --> 00:54:55,541
- Quiet.
MAN: Quiet.

859
00:54:55,709 --> 00:54:57,335
Roll 'em.

860
00:55:00,547 --> 00:55:04,634
LINA: Oh, Pierre, you shouldn't have come.
You're flirting with danger.

861
00:55:04,802 --> 00:55:07,220
What's this wire doing here?
It's dangerous.

862
00:55:07,429 --> 00:55:08,763
[LINA SCREAMS]

863
00:55:09,723 --> 00:55:11,557
[CREW CLAMORING]

864
00:55:21,902 --> 00:55:23,611
You'd better not go in together.

865
00:55:23,862 --> 00:55:26,739
Lina's probably waiting
right inside the door.

866
00:55:26,990 --> 00:55:28,825
- Oh, how I wish...
- Don't worry.

867
00:55:29,076 --> 00:55:32,578
I'll lead the cheering section
in the balcony. Good luck.

868
00:55:37,417 --> 00:55:39,710
- Mr. Lockwood.
DON: Hello.

869
00:55:40,587 --> 00:55:42,380
[MUSIC PLAYING ON FILM]

870
00:55:42,631 --> 00:55:44,674
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDS]

871
00:56:01,483 --> 00:56:04,110
[RATTLING ON FILM]

872
00:56:08,031 --> 00:56:09,907
What's that?
The storm outside?

873
00:56:10,158 --> 00:56:12,618
It's those pearls, Mr. Simpson.

874
00:56:13,662 --> 00:56:16,080
[PEARLS RATTLING]

875
00:56:17,875 --> 00:56:22,211
I am the noblest lady of the court,
second only to the queen.

876
00:56:22,462 --> 00:56:26,132
Yet I am the saddest
of mortals in France.

877
00:56:26,383 --> 00:56:28,217
What is the matter, milady?

878
00:56:28,468 --> 00:56:30,636
I'm so downhearted, Theresa.

879
00:56:30,888 --> 00:56:34,181
My father has me betrothed
to the Baron de Landsfield...

880
00:56:34,433 --> 00:56:35,892
...and I can't stand him.

881
00:56:36,059 --> 00:56:37,101
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

882
00:56:37,269 --> 00:56:38,686
Oh, but he's such a catch.

883
00:56:38,937 --> 00:56:42,523
All the ladies of the court
wish they were in your shoes.

884
00:56:42,774 --> 00:56:45,401
My heart belongs to another...

885
00:56:46,153 --> 00:56:48,070
...Pierre de Bataille.

886
00:56:48,280 --> 00:56:52,241
Ever since I met him,
I can't get him out of my mind.

887
00:56:52,534 --> 00:56:54,994
Sounds good and loud, huh?

888
00:56:57,789 --> 00:56:58,998
[STAFF BANGING]

889
00:56:59,166 --> 00:57:00,541
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

890
00:57:03,253 --> 00:57:04,462
Oh, Pierre!

891
00:57:04,630 --> 00:57:05,922
[DIALOGUE CUTS IN AND OUT]

892
00:57:06,089 --> 00:57:09,008
You shouldn't have come.
You're flirting with danger.

893
00:57:09,301 --> 00:57:11,510
They will surely find you out.

894
00:57:11,803 --> 00:57:14,555
Your head is much too valuable.

895
00:57:14,806 --> 00:57:18,017
She never could remember
where the microphone was.

896
00:57:18,185 --> 00:57:20,895
'Tis Cupid himself
that called me here...

897
00:57:21,188 --> 00:57:22,521
...and I...

898
00:57:22,856 --> 00:57:25,483
...smitten by his arrow,
must fly to your side...

899
00:57:25,651 --> 00:57:27,360
[CLOTHES RUSTLING
AND AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

900
00:57:27,527 --> 00:57:30,363
...despite the threats
of Madame Guillotine.

901
00:57:31,198 --> 00:57:34,033
But the night is full of our enemies.

902
00:57:34,201 --> 00:57:37,036
[FAN THUMPING
AND AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

903
00:57:37,663 --> 00:57:39,914
What you hitting him with,
a blackjack?

904
00:57:40,999 --> 00:57:43,334
Imperious princess of the night...

905
00:57:43,543 --> 00:57:44,877
...I love you.

906
00:57:45,170 --> 00:57:46,712
Oh, Pierre.

907
00:57:46,922 --> 00:57:48,547
I love you.

908
00:57:48,799 --> 00:57:53,010
I love you, I love you, I love you,
I love you, I love you.

909
00:57:53,220 --> 00:57:57,390
I love you, I love you, I love you,
I love you!

910
00:57:57,557 --> 00:57:59,225
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

911
00:57:59,393 --> 00:58:01,727
Did somebody get paid
for writing that?

912
00:58:04,898 --> 00:58:06,357
Sounds like a comedy.

913
00:58:06,566 --> 00:58:09,068
- It's a Lockwood-Lamont talkie.
- What?

914
00:58:09,236 --> 00:58:10,736
WOMAN:
This is terrible.

915
00:58:13,115 --> 00:58:14,740
[DIALOGUE DISTORTED]

916
00:58:18,036 --> 00:58:19,078
What's that?

917
00:58:19,329 --> 00:58:21,539
The sound.
It's out of synchronization!

918
00:58:21,748 --> 00:58:23,040
Tell them to fix it.

919
00:58:23,250 --> 00:58:24,750
Yes, sir.

920
00:58:25,085 --> 00:58:26,085
[AUDIO OUT OF SYNCH]

921
00:58:26,253 --> 00:58:27,586
What's this? Yvonne?

922
00:58:27,754 --> 00:58:31,215
Captured by Rouge Noir
of the Purple Terror?

923
00:58:31,383 --> 00:58:33,926
Ohh. Oh, my sword!

924
00:58:34,136 --> 00:58:36,595
I must fly to her side!

925
00:58:36,847 --> 00:58:38,931
Yvonne, Yvonne...

926
00:58:39,266 --> 00:58:40,766
...my own.

927
00:58:41,435 --> 00:58:44,729
LINA:
Pierre will save me. Pierre!

928
00:58:44,938 --> 00:58:48,065
ACTOR:
Pierre is miles away, you witch.

929
00:58:48,650 --> 00:58:50,359
LINA:
No, no, no.

930
00:58:50,569 --> 00:58:52,611
ACTOR:
Yes, yes, yes.

931
00:58:52,779 --> 00:58:54,447
LINA:
No, no, no.

932
00:58:54,656 --> 00:58:57,450
ACTOR:
Yes, yes, yes.

933
00:58:57,951 --> 00:59:00,327
[AUDIO DISTORTED
AND AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

934
00:59:04,082 --> 00:59:05,166
This is a scream.

935
00:59:05,417 --> 00:59:06,792
Give me The Jazz Singer.

936
00:59:07,002 --> 00:59:09,170
"I love you, I love you, I love you"...

937
00:59:11,798 --> 00:59:14,759
- We're all ruined.
- You can't release this.

938
00:59:14,968 --> 00:59:18,179
We're booked to open
in six weeks all over the country.

939
00:59:18,472 --> 00:59:21,432
But you're such big stars,
we might get by.

940
00:59:21,600 --> 00:59:23,601
WOMAN: I never wanna see
Lockwood and Lamont again.

941
00:59:23,810 --> 00:59:24,810
Wasn't it awful?

942
00:59:25,020 --> 00:59:27,480
This is the worst picture ever made.

943
00:59:27,773 --> 00:59:29,440
I liked it.

944
00:59:37,783 --> 00:59:39,992
Well, take a last look at it.

945
00:59:40,285 --> 00:59:42,328
It'll be up for auction
in the morning.

946
00:59:42,537 --> 00:59:43,954
You're out of your mind.

947
00:59:44,164 --> 00:59:46,916
It's Saturday.
No bank will foreclose until Monday.

948
00:59:47,167 --> 00:59:49,627
- It wasn't so bad.
- That's what I told him.

949
00:59:50,170 --> 00:59:51,670
There's no use kidding myself.

950
00:59:51,963 --> 00:59:55,966
Once they release The Duelling Cavalier,
Lockwood and Lamont are through.

951
00:59:56,176 --> 00:59:57,968
The picture's a museum piece.

952
00:59:58,178 --> 00:59:59,553
I'm a museum piece.

953
00:59:59,805 --> 01:00:02,473
Things went wrong with the sound.
Get the technical...

954
01:00:02,682 --> 01:00:03,808
No, it wasn't that.

955
01:00:04,017 --> 01:00:06,477
This is sweet of both of you, but I...

956
01:00:07,687 --> 01:00:10,231
Something happened to me tonight.

957
01:00:10,482 --> 01:00:12,733
Everything you said
about me is true.

958
01:00:13,026 --> 01:00:14,443
I'm no actor.

959
01:00:14,694 --> 01:00:17,321
I never was.
Just a lot of dumb show.

960
01:00:17,531 --> 01:00:19,198
I know that now.

961
01:00:19,866 --> 01:00:22,535
Well, at least you're
taking it lying down.

962
01:00:22,744 --> 01:00:24,036
No kidding, Cosmo.

963
01:00:24,246 --> 01:00:27,081
Did you ever see anything
as idiotic as me on that screen?

964
01:00:27,374 --> 01:00:28,916
Yeah. How about Lina?

965
01:00:29,084 --> 01:00:31,502
Heh. I ran her a close second.

966
01:00:31,711 --> 01:00:34,463
Maybe it was a photo finish.
I'm through.

967
01:00:34,714 --> 01:00:36,006
You're not through.

968
01:00:36,216 --> 01:00:37,675
Why, of course not.

969
01:00:37,884 --> 01:00:40,219
With your looks,
you could drive an ice wagon.

970
01:00:40,470 --> 01:00:41,679
- Or shine shoes.
- Block hats.

971
01:00:41,888 --> 01:00:43,180
- Sell pencils.
- Dig ditches.

972
01:00:43,390 --> 01:00:44,974
Or go back into vaudeville.

973
01:00:46,268 --> 01:00:49,353
[SINGS] Fit as a fiddle and ready for love
I could jump over the moon up above

974
01:00:49,563 --> 01:00:51,730
Fit as a fiddle and ready for love

975
01:00:53,024 --> 01:00:56,527
Too bad I didn't do that in Duelling
Cavalier. They might have liked it.

976
01:00:56,736 --> 01:00:58,404
- Why don't you?
- What?

977
01:00:58,697 --> 01:01:00,614
- Make a musical.
- A musical?

978
01:01:00,866 --> 01:01:02,366
Sure. Make a musical.

979
01:01:02,576 --> 01:01:05,744
The new Don Lockwood.
He yodels, he jumps about to music.

980
01:01:05,996 --> 01:01:08,789
The only trouble is
that after Duelling Cavalier...

981
01:01:09,082 --> 01:01:13,002
...nobody'd come to see me jump off
the Woolworth Building into a damp rag.

982
01:01:13,211 --> 01:01:15,713
Turn The Duelling Cavalier
into a musical.

983
01:01:15,922 --> 01:01:17,590
- Duelling Cavalier?
- Sure.

984
01:01:17,799 --> 01:01:19,925
They've got six weeks before
it's released.

985
01:01:20,135 --> 01:01:23,095
Add songs and dances,
trim bad scenes, add new ones.

986
01:01:23,388 --> 01:01:24,889
And you got it.

987
01:01:25,348 --> 01:01:27,224
Hey, I think it'll work.

988
01:01:27,392 --> 01:01:28,392
- Of course!
- It's a cinch.

989
01:01:28,602 --> 01:01:30,561
It may be crazy, but we'll do it.

990
01:01:30,770 --> 01:01:33,314
The Duelling Cavalier
is now a musical.

991
01:01:33,607 --> 01:01:34,940
- Hot dog!
