01:30:05,650 --> 01:30:07,234
Zelda told me everything.

1249
01:30:07,485 --> 01:30:10,279
- Thanks, Zelda. You're a real pal.
- Anytime, Don.

1250
01:30:10,488 --> 01:30:11,739
Look, Don and I...

1251
01:30:11,990 --> 01:30:14,658
Don! Don't you dare call him Don!

1252
01:30:14,868 --> 01:30:17,870
I was calling him Don
before you were born.

1253
01:30:18,121 --> 01:30:19,830
I mean...
You were kissing him!

1254
01:30:20,123 --> 01:30:23,542
I was kissing her.
I happen to be in love with her.

1255
01:30:23,793 --> 01:30:27,838
That's ridiculous! Everybody knows
you're in love with me.

1256
01:30:28,006 --> 01:30:32,134
Ha, ha. Now look, Lina.
Try and understand this.

1257
01:30:32,344 --> 01:30:34,011
I'm going to marry her.

1258
01:30:34,304 --> 01:30:36,972
Silly boy.
She ain't the marrying kind.

1259
01:30:37,182 --> 01:30:40,017
She's a flirt
trying to get ahead by using you.

1260
01:30:40,268 --> 01:30:44,647
Well, I'll put a stop to that!
I'm gonna go up and see R.F. right now!

1261
01:30:44,856 --> 01:30:46,357
A little late.
The picture's finished.

1262
01:30:46,524 --> 01:30:48,859
If she weren't in it,
you'd be finished too.

1263
01:30:49,069 --> 01:30:52,029
As far as I can see,
she's the only one who's finished.

1264
01:30:52,322 --> 01:30:53,322
Who'll hear of her?

1265
01:30:53,531 --> 01:30:56,700
Everybody. Why do you think
Zelda's in such a sweat?

1266
01:30:56,910 --> 01:30:58,702
Kathy nearly stole
the picture from her.

1267
01:30:58,870 --> 01:31:00,913
She's only doing you a favor
in The Dancing Cavalier.

1268
01:31:01,206 --> 01:31:04,208
And she's getting
full screen credit for it too.

1269
01:31:04,501 --> 01:31:08,212
It'll say on the screen
that I don't talk and sing for myself?

1270
01:31:08,380 --> 01:31:10,297
Of course. What do you think?

1271
01:31:10,548 --> 01:31:12,549
- They can't do that.
- It's already done.

1272
01:31:12,842 --> 01:31:15,094
There's a whole
publicity campaign planned.

1273
01:31:15,387 --> 01:31:16,804
Publicity?

1274
01:31:17,055 --> 01:31:18,889
They can't make a fool out of me.

1275
01:31:19,099 --> 01:31:21,725
They can't make a laughingstock
out of Lina Lamont.

1276
01:31:22,018 --> 01:31:24,895
What do they think I am,
dumb or something?

1277
01:31:25,188 --> 01:31:27,439
Why, I make more money...

1278
01:31:28,233 --> 01:31:30,109
...than Calvin Coolidge...

1279
01:31:30,360 --> 01:31:32,194
...put together!

1280
01:31:34,239 --> 01:31:38,951
ROD: "Monumental Pictures enthusiastic
over Lina's singing and dancing."

1281
01:31:39,202 --> 01:31:40,244
I never said that.

1282
01:31:40,412 --> 01:31:44,415
"Premiere tomorrow night to reveal
Lina Lamont, big musical talent."

1283
01:31:44,624 --> 01:31:47,751
You can't pull a switch like this
on the publicity department.

1284
01:31:47,961 --> 01:31:50,087
We were prepared
for the Selden campaign.

1285
01:31:50,338 --> 01:31:52,423
Now you do this.
At least keep us informed.

1286
01:31:52,590 --> 01:31:55,384
Wait a minute.
I don't know anything about this.

1287
01:31:55,593 --> 01:31:56,844
What are we gonna do?

1288
01:31:57,053 --> 01:31:58,053
LINA:
Nothing.

1289
01:31:59,055 --> 01:32:01,598
Absolutely nothing.

1290
01:32:01,891 --> 01:32:04,935
You wouldn't wanna call the papers
and say Lina Lamont...

1291
01:32:05,145 --> 01:32:07,438
...is a big fat liar.

1292
01:32:07,731 --> 01:32:09,273
Did you send this stuff out?

1293
01:32:09,566 --> 01:32:12,901
I gave an exclusive story
to every paper in town.

1294
01:32:13,111 --> 01:32:15,279
You'll never get away with it.
Call the papers.

1295
01:32:15,488 --> 01:32:17,281
I wouldn't do that if I were you.

1296
01:32:17,490 --> 01:32:19,575
Don't tell me what to do, Lina.

1297
01:32:19,784 --> 01:32:23,287
What do you think I am,
dumb or something?

1298
01:32:23,496 --> 01:32:26,623
I had my lawyer go over my contract.

1299
01:32:26,875 --> 01:32:27,958
Contract?

1300
01:32:28,251 --> 01:32:30,794
And I control my publicity, not you.

1301
01:32:30,962 --> 01:32:32,171
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1302
01:32:32,338 --> 01:32:35,382
The studio is responsible
for every word printed about me.

1303
01:32:35,592 --> 01:32:38,677
If I don't like it, I can sue.

1304
01:32:38,970 --> 01:32:40,012
What?

1305
01:32:40,263 --> 01:32:42,473
I can sue.

1306
01:32:42,682 --> 01:32:45,642
If you tell the papers
about Kathy Selden...

1307
01:32:45,894 --> 01:32:50,606
...it would be "detrimental
and deleterious" to my career.

1308
01:32:51,274 --> 01:32:54,401
I could sue you for the whole studio.

1309
01:32:54,652 --> 01:32:56,904
- That's a lot of nonsense.
- Says so.

1310
01:32:57,155 --> 01:32:58,530
Right here.

1311
01:32:58,823 --> 01:33:03,327
Contract dated June 8, 1925,
paragraph 34, subdivision letter A.

1312
01:33:03,495 --> 01:33:05,537
"The party of the first part..."

1313
01:33:05,789 --> 01:33:07,623
- That's me.
- You win, Lina.

1314
01:33:07,832 --> 01:33:10,459
We better take Kathy's
credit card off the screen.

1315
01:33:10,668 --> 01:33:12,002
All right, go ahead.

1316
01:33:12,212 --> 01:33:14,421
Let's just get
this premiere over with.

1317
01:33:14,672 --> 01:33:16,006
Satisfied?

1318
01:33:16,216 --> 01:33:18,717
There's just one little thing more.

1319
01:33:19,177 --> 01:33:23,222
You want me to change the name of
the studio to Lamont Pictures, Inc.?

1320
01:33:23,515 --> 01:33:25,474
R.F., you're cute.

1321
01:33:25,683 --> 01:33:27,518
Now, I was just thinking.

1322
01:33:27,727 --> 01:33:30,229
You've given her
a part in Zelda's picture...

1323
01:33:30,522 --> 01:33:33,023
...and you'll give her
a bigger one in the next.

1324
01:33:33,316 --> 01:33:34,817
So, what?

1325
01:33:35,026 --> 01:33:37,736
If she's done such a grand job
doubling for my voice...

1326
01:33:38,029 --> 01:33:41,323
...don't you think she ought to
go on doing just that?

1327
01:33:41,533 --> 01:33:43,826
- And nothing else.
- You're out of your mind.

1328
01:33:44,035 --> 01:33:47,079
I'm still more important
to the studio than she is.

1329
01:33:47,330 --> 01:33:49,081
I wouldn't do that to her
in a million years.

1330
01:33:49,332 --> 01:33:52,835
You'd take her career away.
People don't do things like that.

1331
01:33:53,044 --> 01:33:54,586
People?

1332
01:33:54,879 --> 01:33:56,713
I ain't people.

1333
01:33:57,006 --> 01:33:58,757
I am a...

1334
01:34:02,178 --> 01:34:06,557
"A shimmering, glowing star
in the cinema firmament."

1335
01:34:06,724 --> 01:34:08,559
It says so...

1336
01:34:08,893 --> 01:34:10,227
...right there.

1337
01:34:22,740 --> 01:34:27,578
Oh, Pierre, Pierre, my darling.
At last, I've found you.

1338
01:34:27,745 --> 01:34:28,787
Oh, Pierre.

1339
01:34:29,038 --> 01:34:32,791
Pierre, you're hurt.
Speak to me, speak to me.

1340
01:34:33,626 --> 01:34:37,629
[SINGIN]
I'll kiss her with a sigh

1341
01:34:38,423 --> 01:34:40,215
Would you?

1342
01:34:40,550 --> 01:34:42,384
Would you?

1343
01:34:42,886 --> 01:34:46,722
And if the girl were I

1344
01:34:47,015 --> 01:34:48,557
Would you?

1345
01:34:49,100 --> 01:34:51,143
Would you?

1346
01:34:51,603 --> 01:34:54,897
Oh, Pierre, hold me
in your arms always.

1347
01:34:55,106 --> 01:34:56,398
Lockwood's a sensation.

1348
01:34:56,608 --> 01:35:00,277
Yes, but Lamont! What a voice!
Isn't she marvelous?

1349
01:35:00,570 --> 01:35:03,071
- It's going over wonderfully, isn't it?
- Yeah.

1350
01:35:03,281 --> 01:35:07,618
Our love will last
till the stars turn cold.

1351
01:35:08,286 --> 01:35:12,956
[SINGING]
And would you dare to say

1352
01:35:13,124 --> 01:35:18,295
Let's do the same as they

1353
01:35:19,756 --> 01:35:21,356
I would

1354
01:35:24,969 --> 01:35:29,139
Would you?

1355
01:35:36,231 --> 01:35:38,482
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDS]

1356
01:35:52,956 --> 01:35:54,331
R.F., it's a real smash.

1357
01:35:54,499 --> 01:35:57,209
- Congratulations. We owe you a lot.
- Thank you.

1358
01:35:57,460 --> 01:35:59,336
- Kathy, we made it!
- It's a miracle!

1359
01:35:59,629 --> 01:36:01,380
It's great, Don. Just great.

1360
01:36:01,631 --> 01:36:04,508
You were fabulous.
You sang as well as Kathy Selden.

1361
01:36:04,717 --> 01:36:07,678
And I'm gonna for a long time.

1362
01:36:07,845 --> 01:36:08,845
What do you mean?

1363
01:36:09,097 --> 01:36:12,349
I mean she's gonna go
right on singing for me.

1364
01:36:12,642 --> 01:36:13,725
Listen, Lina.

1365
01:36:14,018 --> 01:36:17,688
I thought something was cooking
beneath those bleached curls.

1366
01:36:17,897 --> 01:36:21,024
Kathy has her own career.
She only did this for this picture.

1367
01:36:21,317 --> 01:36:22,693
That's what you think.

1368
01:36:22,902 --> 01:36:24,528
Come on, come on.

1369
01:36:24,821 --> 01:36:27,030
- Lina's getting carried away.
- Yeah, she is.

1370
01:36:27,323 --> 01:36:28,699
Listen, you boa constrictor.

1371
01:36:28,992 --> 01:36:31,743
Don't get any fancy ideas
about the future. Tell her!

1372
01:36:32,036 --> 01:36:34,371
Never mind, R.F.!
Listen to that applause.

1373
01:36:34,664 --> 01:36:36,248
Wait till the money rolls in.

1374
01:36:36,499 --> 01:36:40,419
You won't give all that up because
a nobody don't wanna be my voice.

1375
01:36:40,712 --> 01:36:42,629
She's got something.
It's a gold mine.

1376
01:36:42,880 --> 01:36:45,007
Part of that choice is mine.

1377
01:36:45,216 --> 01:36:46,508
And I just won't do it.

1378
01:36:46,718 --> 01:36:50,345
You've got a five-year contract.
You'll do what R.F. says.

1379
01:36:50,555 --> 01:36:53,056
What's the matter?
Why don't you tell her off?

1380
01:36:53,266 --> 01:36:55,142
I'm confused.
This thing is so big...

1381
01:36:55,393 --> 01:36:58,562
- They're tearing the house apart.
- Take a curtain call.

1382
01:36:58,771 --> 01:37:01,064
I once gave you a cigar.
Can I have it back?

1383
01:37:01,232 --> 01:37:04,568
Listen! I'm an avalanche!
Selden, you're stuck.

1384
01:37:04,861 --> 01:37:08,071
If this happens, get a new boy.
I won't stand for it.

1385
01:37:08,281 --> 01:37:11,700
Who needs you? They'd come to see me
if I played opposite a monkey!

1386
01:37:11,909 --> 01:37:13,243
Don's a smash too.

1387
01:37:13,536 --> 01:37:16,079
I'll say a few words.
I'm still running the studio.

1388
01:37:16,289 --> 01:37:17,748
I'm not so sure!

1389
01:37:17,957 --> 01:37:21,251
You're Mr. Producer,
always running things, running me.

1390
01:37:21,461 --> 01:37:24,921
From now on, as far as I'm concerned,
I'm running things.

1391
01:37:25,214 --> 01:37:27,507
- Lina Lamont Pictures, Inc., huh?
- Yeah.

1392
01:37:27,717 --> 01:37:29,426
You've gone a little too far.

1393
01:37:29,677 --> 01:37:31,928
- They're yelling for a speech.
- A speech?

1394
01:37:32,221 --> 01:37:35,057
Yeah, everybody's always making
speeches for me.

1395
01:37:35,266 --> 01:37:39,603
Tonight, I'm gonna do my own talking.
I'm gonna make the speech!

1396
01:37:39,896 --> 01:37:42,773
ROD: No, please!
DON: Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

1397
01:37:43,066 --> 01:37:46,943
This is Lina's big night
and she's entitled to do the talking.

1398
01:37:48,196 --> 01:37:50,447
- Right?
- Right.

1399
01:37:55,328 --> 01:37:57,412
Ladies and gentlemen.

1400
01:37:57,622 --> 01:37:58,705
I can't tell you...

1401
01:37:58,915 --> 01:38:01,083
...how thrilled we are
at your reception...

1402
01:38:01,292 --> 01:38:05,295
...for The Dancing Cavalier,
our first musical picture together.

1403
01:38:05,588 --> 01:38:09,841
If we bring a little joy
into your humdrum lives...

1404
01:38:10,134 --> 01:38:12,344
...it makes us feel
as though our hard work...

1405
01:38:12,637 --> 01:38:15,097
...ain't been in vain for nothing.

1406
01:38:16,224 --> 01:38:17,933
Bless you all.

1407
01:38:18,142 --> 01:38:19,851
She didn't sound that way
in the picture.

1408
01:38:20,144 --> 01:38:21,728
Cut the talk, Lina. Sing!

1409
01:38:22,772 --> 01:38:25,565
MAN 1: Sing us a song, Lina.
Sing to us.

1410
01:38:25,733 --> 01:38:28,193
MAN 2: Please.
MAN 3: Come on, Lina, sing.

1411
01:38:29,320 --> 01:38:30,987
DON:
I got an idea. Come here.

1412
01:38:31,197 --> 01:38:32,239
Now, listen.

1413
01:38:36,452 --> 01:38:38,453
LINA:
What am I gonna do?

1414
01:38:38,663 --> 01:38:41,623
We've got it.
Get a mike set up back of that curtain.

1415
01:38:41,833 --> 01:38:45,168
Kathy, come here.
Kathy will stand back of there and sing.

1416
01:38:45,378 --> 01:38:48,839
She'll be back of the curtain singing,
and I'll be in front...

1417
01:38:49,048 --> 01:38:50,757
- Like in the picture?
- Right.

1418
01:38:51,008 --> 01:38:52,843
You've gotta do it. This is too big.

1419
01:38:53,052 --> 01:38:57,013
She's got a five-year contract with me.
Get over to that mike.

1420
01:38:57,265 --> 01:38:59,516
You heard him, Kathy. Now do it!

1421
01:38:59,809 --> 01:39:00,976
I'll do it, Don.

1422
01:39:01,185 --> 01:39:03,019
But I never want to see you again...

1423
01:39:03,312 --> 01:39:05,188
...on or off the screen.

1424
01:39:05,356 --> 01:39:07,023
Now, come on, Lina.

1425
01:39:11,571 --> 01:39:13,321
ORCHESTRA LEADER:
What are you gonna sing?

1426
01:39:17,285 --> 01:39:18,326
"Singin' in the Rain."

1427
01:39:19,704 --> 01:39:20,912
"Singin' in the Rain."

1428
01:39:21,831 --> 01:39:23,081
"Singin' in the Rain."

1429
01:39:23,374 --> 01:39:24,499
In what key?

1430
01:39:27,378 --> 01:39:28,712
KATHY:
A-flat.

1431
01:39:28,921 --> 01:39:30,005
A-flat.

1432
